==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Muscat
<hw>Mus"cat</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. See
<er>Muscadel</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A name given to several
varieties of Old World grapes, differing in color, size, etc., but all
having a somewhat musky flavor. The muscat of Alexandria is a large oval
grape of a pale amber color.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>muskat</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Muscatel</ent>⟦br⟧
